{
  "stem": "18470.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 284.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they let us in, and they put us up into the pauper's gallery.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we went back the following day, sat up there again.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then suddenly an opportunity occurred.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because the cantor developed laryngitis.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he was unable to read the Torah.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the place was packed, of course, and the rabbi in a cold sweat asked, is there anybody here who can read the Torah?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "No one budged.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So my father tried to dope out what was going on here.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he finally out of sheer amazement, said, no one here could do this?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Well, the service stopped cold.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So he got up, and he walked all the way down from the upper balcony up to the bimah, and addressed the rabbi and said in his best German, [SPEAKING GERMAN] Rabbi, may I read?",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And because most of the men in Oberwesel could read the Torah, if not at sight, then with practice.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But my dad knew that portion, and he sang it beautifully.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And from that point on, our Americanization took place in that synagogue, which became the place where I developed a love of Judaism.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "As the rabbi-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] this incident, I guess, was-- it was September of 1939.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that rabbi died in 1940 or so, and then a new rabbi came in, who made this a very exciting place.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because he had just left his practice as a lawyer and decided to be a rabbi.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And gave us kids, boys and girls, a wonderful opportunity to speak publicly, and to help in the war effort.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We sold war bonds by giving speeches every Shabbos morning.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then they'd send us out to the [NON-ENGLISH] on the east side.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
